"ltr" style=3D"--animation-duration: 400ms; --fade-animation-function: ease=
-out;"><p data-path-to-node=3D"0">That is a fantastic question, and in 90% =
of standard web applications (like e-commerce, banking, or customer support=
), you would be absolutely right. A pre-chat selection screen (like a wizar=
d or a menu) is standard practice.</p><p data-path-to-node=3D"1">However, d=
esigning for <b data-path-to-node=3D"1" data-index-in-node=3D"23">crisis in=
tervention and mental health requires breaking standard UX rules</b>.</p><p=
 data-path-to-node=3D"2">Here is why we intentionally skipped a preliminary=
 "selection screen" and dropped them directly into the chat, and how we can=
 tweak the design to accomplish exactly what you are asking for without add=
ing friction.</p><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"3">The Psychology of "Time-to-Hel=
p"</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"4">If a user is experiencing severe withdraw=
al, a panic attack, or a high-stress family emergency, their cognitive load=
 is already maxed out.</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"5"><li><p data-path-to-n=
ode=3D"5,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"5,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">The P=
roblem with Pre-Screens:</b> Putting a menu or a form between a person in p=
ain and the "help" feels like calling emergency services and getting an aut=
omated phone tree ("Press 1 for X, Press 2 for Y"). It causes massive drop-=
off rates.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"5,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=
=3D"5,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">The "Immediate Haven" Effect:</b> Dropp=
ing them instantly into an active chat interface gives the psychological re=
lief that <i data-path-to-node=3D"5,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"120">help is=
 already here and listening</i>.</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"6">T=
he Solution: "In-Stream Onboarding"</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"7">Instead =
of a separate screen that asks what they want <i data-path-to-node=3D"7" da=
ta-index-in-node=3D"54">before</i> the chat starts, <b data-path-to-node=3D=
"7" data-index-in-node=3D"78">the AI's first message <i data-path-to-node=
=3D"7" data-index-in-node=3D"101">is</i> the triage.</b> To make your idea =
work perfectly within the current design, we just need to change the AI's i=
nitial greeting so it explicitly acts as that first filtering question.</p>=
<p data-path-to-node=3D"8">Instead of the generic "Hello, I'm here for you"=
 seen in the mockup, the flow should look like this:</p><p data-path-to-nod=
e=3D"9"><b data-path-to-node=3D"9" data-index-in-node=3D"0">1. The App Load=
s (Zero Friction)</b>
The user immediately sees the chat window.</p><p data-path-to-node=3D"10"><=
b data-path-to-node=3D"10" data-index-in-node=3D"0">2. The New Triage Greet=
ing (AI)</b>
The AI's very first message acts as the menu you suggested:</p><blockquote =
data-path-to-node=3D"11"><p data-path-to-node=3D"11,0"><i data-path-to-node=
=3D"11,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">"Welcome to Beacon. This is a secure, an=
onymous space. To make sure I get you the right kind of support immediately=
, tell me what brings you here today?"</i></p></blockquote><p data-path-to-=
node=3D"12"><b data-path-to-node=3D"12" data-index-in-node=3D"0">3. The Use=
r Chooses (The Chips)</b>
The user doesn't have to type if they are overwhelmed. They just click one =
of the chips:</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"13"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"1=
3,0,0"><code data-path-to-node=3D"13,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">[ I need=
 help for myself right now ]</code> -&gt; <i data-path-to-node=3D"13,0,0" d=
ata-index-in-node=3D"40">Routes to Crisis/Triage Agent</i></p></li><li><p d=
ata-path-to-node=3D"13,1,0"><code data-path-to-node=3D"13,1,0" data-index-i=
n-node=3D"0">[ I'm looking for local rehab resources ]</code> -&gt; <i data=
-path-to-node=3D"13,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"45">Routes to Resource Agent=
</i></p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"13,2,0"><code data-path-to-node=3D=
"13,2,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">[ I want to help a loved one ]</code> -&g=
t; <i data-path-to-node=3D"13,2,0" data-index-in-node=3D"34">Routes to Anch=
or Agent</i></p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"14">Why This is Better</=
h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"15">By doing it this way, you accomplish exactly=
 what you suggested=E2=80=94segmenting the user to start the right session=
=E2=80=94but you do it conversationally. It feels like someone is actively =
talking to them from second zero, rather than forcing them to fill out a fo=
rm before they are allowed into the room.</p><p data-path-to-node=3D"16">Wo=
uld you like me to draft the exact v0.dev prompt to update the AI's welcome=
 message and interaction logic to reflect this conversational triage?</p></=
