"--animation-duration: 400ms; --fade-animation-function: ease-out;"><p data=
-path-to-node=3D"0">Here are the two foundational documents updated for our=
 new direction: the <b data-path-to-node=3D"0" data-index-in-node=3D"75">Pr=
oduct Requirements Document (PRD)</b> and the <b data-path-to-node=3D"0" da=
ta-index-in-node=3D"119">Technical Direction Document for the Agentic Workf=
low</b>.</p><p data-path-to-node=3D"1">These documents are structured to se=
rve as the blueprint for both your design and engineering phases.</p><hr da=
ta-path-to-node=3D"2"><h1 data-path-to-node=3D"3">Document 1: Product Requi=
rements Document (PRD)</h1><h2 data-path-to-node=3D"4">Project "Beacon": Sm=
art Drug Awareness &amp; Prevention Chatbot</h2><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"5"=
>1. Executive Summary</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"6">Project "Beacon" is a =
proactive, educational, and anonymous AI chatbot designed to equip users=E2=
=80=94particularly youth and young adults=E2=80=94with factual knowledge ab=
out substance abuse, actionable strategies for handling peer pressure, and =
healthy coping mechanisms for stress. It shifts the paradigm from <i data-p=
ath-to-node=3D"6" data-index-in-node=3D"297">reactive crisis management</i>=
 to <i data-path-to-node=3D"6" data-index-in-node=3D"327">proactive prevent=
ion and mental resilience</i>.</p><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"7">2. Problem St=
atement</h3><ul data-path-to-node=3D"8"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"8,0,0">=
<b data-path-to-node=3D"8,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">The Stigma of Curio=
sity:</b> Young people have questions about substances and peer pressure bu=
t are terrified to ask teachers, parents, or standard search engines due to=
 fear of being tracked, judged, or punished.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-no=
de=3D"8,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"8,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Lack o=
f Actionable Coping Skills:</b> Existing resources often preach "Just Say N=
o" without providing realistic psychological scripts or stress-management t=
echniques for modern social situations.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D=
"8,2,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"8,2,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Misinformat=
ion:</b> Social media is rife with dangerous misinformation regarding the s=
afety of vaping, synthetic drugs, and prescription misuse.</p></li></ul><h3=
 data-path-to-node=3D"9">3. Target Audience</h3><ul data-path-to-node=3D"10=
"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"10,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"10,0,0" data-=
index-in-node=3D"0">The Learner:</b> A student or young adult curious about=
 the biological effects or risks of a specific substance.</p></li><li><p da=
ta-path-to-node=3D"10,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"10,1,0" data-index-in-no=
de=3D"0">The Pressured:</b> An individual facing social pressure to consume=
 substances and seeking immediate advice on how to navigate the situation s=
afely.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"10,2,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"=
10,2,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">The Stressed:</b> A user feeling overwhelm=
ed by academic or life stress, looking for healthy alternatives to substanc=
e use.</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"11">4. Core Features &amp; The=
 Multi-Agent System</h3><ul data-path-to-node=3D"12"><li><p data-path-to-no=
de=3D"12,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"12,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">In-S=
tream Onboarding:</b> A frictionless entry point where the AI's first greet=
ing acts as a conversational menu (Learn, Handle Pressure, Manage Stress), =
completely bypassing login screens.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"12,=
1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"12,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">The Educator =
Agent (RAG Knowledge Base):</b> Connects to a strictly verified database of=
 medical and psychological facts. Explains the neuroscience of addiction an=
d substance effects without scare tactics.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=
=3D"12,2,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"12,2,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">The Pr=
evention &amp; Coping Coach:</b> A behavioral agent that provides practical=
, actionable advice. Generates interactive "Coping Strategy Cards" (e.g., g=
rounding exercises, scripts for refusing substances at parties).</p></li><l=
i><p data-path-to-node=3D"12,3,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"12,3,0" data-inde=
x-in-node=3D"0">The Crisis Guardrail:</b> A deterministic safety net. If a =
user inputs intent signaling an active overdose, severe withdrawal, or self=
-harm, the system bypasses standard generation and immediately provides eme=
rgency services routing.</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"13">5. Succe=
ss Metrics (Anonymized)</h3><ul data-path-to-node=3D"14"><li><p data-path-t=
o-node=3D"14,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"14,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">=
Engagement:</b> Number of interactive "Coping Strategy Cards" utilized per =
session.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"14,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=
=3D"14,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Retention:</b> Average session length =
(indicating deep reading/interaction rather than immediate bounce).</p></li=
><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"14,2,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"14,2,0" data-i=
ndex-in-node=3D"0">Safety:</b> Zero hallucinations regarding medical facts =
(measured by RAG accuracy tests).</p></li></ul><hr data-path-to-node=3D"15"=
><h1 data-path-to-node=3D"16">Document 2: Technical Direction (Agentic Work=
flow)</h1><h2 data-path-to-node=3D"17">Architecture &amp; Orchestration Blu=
eprint</h2><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"18">1. System Philosophy</h3><p data-pa=
th-to-node=3D"19">The backend must operate as a <b data-path-to-node=3D"19"=
 data-index-in-node=3D"30">Multi-Agent Orchestrator</b>. The frontend UI is=
 a "Single Pane of Glass"=E2=80=94meaning the user only ever sees one unifi=
ed chatbot interface. All complexity, routing, and database querying happen=
 invisibly on the backend.</p><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"20">2. Core Componen=
ts</h3><ul data-path-to-node=3D"21"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"21,0,0"><b =
data-path-to-node=3D"21,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Frontend (Next.js/Rea=
ct):</b> Manages the Glassmorphism UI, captures user input, renders interac=
tive cards, and maintains ephemeral session state.</p></li><li><p data-path=
-to-node=3D"21,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"21,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0=
">Supervisor Node (The Router LLM):</b> A lightweight, fast LLM whose <i da=
ta-path-to-node=3D"21,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"64">only</i> job is to cla=
ssify the user's intent and route the payload to the correct specialized ag=
ent.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"21,2,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"21=
,2,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Data Refinery Node:</b> Ensures that all dat=
abase queries (for factual drug information) strictly map to predefined SQL=
 columns to eliminate LLM hallucinations.</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-nod=
e=3D"22">3. The Step-by-Step Agentic Workflow</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"2=
3"><b data-path-to-node=3D"23" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Phase 1: Ingestion =
&amp; Safety Check</b></p><ol start=3D"1" data-path-to-node=3D"24"><li><p d=
ata-path-to-node=3D"24,0,0">User clicks a triage chip (e.g., "Handling peer=
 pressure") or types a message.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"24,1,0"=
>The payload hits the <b data-path-to-node=3D"24,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D=
"21">Semantic Guardrail</b>.</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"24,1,1"><li><p dat=
a-path-to-node=3D"24,1,1,0,0"><i data-path-to-node=3D"24,1,1,0,0" data-inde=
x-in-node=3D"0">Condition A (High Risk):</i> Keywords like "overdose," "sui=
cide," or "took too much" are detected. The workflow is hijacked. The UI lo=
cks into Crisis Mode and displays SOS buttons.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-=
node=3D"24,1,1,1,0"><i data-path-to-node=3D"24,1,1,1,0" data-index-in-node=
=3D"0">Condition B (Safe):</i> Payload passes to the Supervisor Node.</p></=
li></ul></li></ol><p data-path-to-node=3D"25"><b data-path-to-node=3D"25" d=
ata-index-in-node=3D"0">Phase 2: Intent Routing (Supervisor Node)</b></p><o=
l start=3D"1" data-path-to-node=3D"26"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"26,0,0">=
The Supervisor categorizes the intent: <code data-path-to-node=3D"26,0,0" d=
ata-index-in-node=3D"39">[EDUCATION]</code>, <code data-path-to-node=3D"26,=
0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"52">[COPING]</code>, or <code data-path-to-node=
=3D"26,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"65">[GENERAL_CHAT]</code>.</p></li><li><p=
 data-path-to-node=3D"26,1,0">The Supervisor packages the user's message an=
d the ephemeral session history, then hands it off to the specialized agent=
.</p></li></ol><p data-path-to-node=3D"27"><b data-path-to-node=3D"27" data=
-index-in-node=3D"0">Phase 3: Specialized Agent Execution</b></p><ul data-p=
ath-to-node=3D"28"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"28,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=
=3D"28,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">If routed to The Educator:</b></p><ol =
start=3D"1" data-path-to-node=3D"28,0,1"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"28,0,1=
,0,0">The Agent extracts the substance entity (e.g., "Vaping").</p></li><li=
><p data-path-to-node=3D"28,0,1,1,0">Triggers the Data Refinery Node to que=
ry the local PostgreSQL/Vector DB for verified medical facts on "Vaping".</=
p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"28,0,1,2,0">Synthesizes a calm, factual =
response.</p></li></ol></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"28,1,0"><b data-pat=
h-to-node=3D"28,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">If routed to The Coping Coach=
:</b></p><ol start=3D"1" data-path-to-node=3D"28,1,1"><li><p data-path-to-n=
ode=3D"28,1,1,0,0">The Agent analyzes the social context (e.g., "party," "f=
riends pressuring me").</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"28,1,1,1,0">Ret=
rieves cognitive behavioral scripts.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"28=
,1,1,2,0">Formats the response to include a JSON trigger for the frontend t=
o render an interactive <code data-path-to-node=3D"28,1,1,2,0" data-index-i=
n-node=3D"89">CopingStrategyCard</code> UI component.</p></li></ol></li></u=
l><p data-path-to-node=3D"29"><b data-path-to-node=3D"29" data-index-in-nod=
e=3D"0">Phase 4: Frontend Delivery</b></p><ol start=3D"1" data-path-to-node=
=3D"30"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"30,0,0">The specialized agent sends the=
 synthesized response back to the frontend.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-nod=
e=3D"30,1,0">The UI renders the text bubble (Soft Indigo color) and any acc=
ompanying dynamic React components (like a breathing exercise widget or a s=
trategy card).</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"30,2,0">The loading indi=
cator (pulsing dots) is dismissed.</p></li></ol><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"31=
">4. Data Privacy Mandate (Zero-Data Logging)</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"3=
2">To guarantee the safety required by the PRD, the workflow must enforce e=
phemeral memory.</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"33"><li><p data-path-to-node=
=3D"33,0,0">Conversation history is stored in the local session state (brow=
ser-side) or a volatile Redis cache that automatically purges the moment th=
e session closes or times out.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"33,1,0">=
No Personally Identifiable Information (PII) is ever written to a permanent=
 database.</p></li></ul><hr data-path-to-node=3D"34"><p data-path-to-node=
=3D"35"><b data-path-to-node=3D"35" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Next Steps for=
