 ease-out;"><p data-path-to-node=3D"0">Here are the two comprehensive docum=
ents. The first is a high-impact pitch document designed specifically to be=
 handed to the <b data-path-to-node=3D"0" data-index-in-node=3D"126">Antigr=
avity</b> judging panel, directly mapped to their scoring rubric to ensure =
maximum points. The second is the technical backend blueprint for your engi=
neering team to build the agentic workflow.</p><hr data-path-to-node=3D"1">=
<h1 data-path-to-node=3D"2">Document 1: Project Pitch for Antigravity Judge=
s</h1><h2 data-path-to-node=3D"3">Project "Beacon": Smart Drug Awareness &a=
mp; Prevention Chatbot</h2><p data-path-to-node=3D"4"><b data-path-to-node=
=3D"4" data-index-in-node=3D"0">To the Antigravity Judging Panel:</b>
Project Beacon is not a standard generative text wrapper. It is a secure, m=
ulti-agent proactive education platform designed to break the stigma surrou=
nding youth substance awareness. By prioritizing absolute anonymity and cog=
nitive ease, Beacon delivers factual education and psychological coping mec=
hanisms directly to vulnerable users.</p><p data-path-to-node=3D"5">Here is=
 how Beacon aligns with the Antigravity hackathon criteria:</p><h3 data-pat=
h-to-node=3D"6">1. Technical Depth (30%)</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"7">Bea=
con utilizes a sophisticated <b data-path-to-node=3D"7" data-index-in-node=
=3D"32">Multi-Agent Orchestrator Architecture</b>. Instead of relying on a =
single, monolithic LLM prompt, the backend employs a Supervisor Router Node=
 that classifies user intent and delegates tasks to specialized sub-agents.=
</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"8"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"8,0,0"><b data-=
path-to-node=3D"8,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Safety Engineering:</b> A d=
eterministic Semantic Guardrail intercepts high-risk intents (e.g., severe =
withdrawal, self-harm) before they reach the LLM, triggering an immediate U=
I override with emergency resources.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"8,=
1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"8,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Precision Retr=
ieval:</b> Our Educator Agent utilizes a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RA=
G) pipeline connected to a verified PostgreSQL database. To ensure zero med=
ical hallucinations, our data refinery nodes are strictly programmed with e=
xact database schemas to fetch only verified scientific literature.</p></li=
></ul><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"9">2. Relevance &amp; Impact (25%)</h3><p da=
ta-path-to-node=3D"10">The greatest barrier to youth drug education is the =
fear of judgment or punishment. Traditional resources (school counselors, w=
eb searches) leave a digital footprint or require deanonymization.</p><ul d=
ata-path-to-node=3D"11"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"11,0,0"><b data-path-to=
-node=3D"11,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Real-World Applicability:</b> Bea=
con operates on a strict "Zero-Data Logging" policy using ephemeral, sessio=
n-based memory. By guaranteeing absolute privacy, we create a psychological=
ly safe space for users to ask difficult questions about peer pressure and =
synthetic substances, maximizing real-world utilization.</p></li></ul><h3 d=
ata-path-to-node=3D"12">3. Conversational UX (20%)</h3><p data-path-to-node=
=3D"13">To prevent cognitive overload for users experiencing stress or peer=
 pressure, Beacon employs a "Single Pane of Glass" architecture styled with=
 a calming Glassmorphism aesthetic.</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"14"><li><p =
data-path-to-node=3D"14,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"14,0,0" data-index-in-=
node=3D"0">In-Stream Onboarding:</b> We eliminated standard login forms and=
 complex navigation menus. The AI=E2=80=99s initial greeting acts as a conv=
ersational menu using Quick-Action Chips ("Learn about a substance," "Handl=
ing peer pressure"), allowing users to intuitively guide the session from t=
he first click.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"14,1,0"><b data-path-to=
-node=3D"14,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Dynamic UI Rendering:</b> The bot=
 does not just output text walls. It renders interactive React components=
=E2=80=94such as actionable "Coping Strategy Cards" and guided breathing ex=
ercises=E2=80=94directly inside the chat stream.</p></li></ul><h3 data-path=
-to-node=3D"15">4. Innovation (15%)</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"16">Beacon =
solves the hardest paradox in healthcare tech: <b data-path-to-node=3D"16" =
data-index-in-node=3D"54">Personalization vs. Anonymity</b>.</p><ul data-pa=
th-to-node=3D"17"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"17,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=
=3D"17,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Zero-Data Triage:</b> Through progress=
ive profiling via our In-Stream Onboarding chips, the system injects critic=
al context (e.g., "User is dealing with peer pressure at a party") into the=
 Supervisor Node's hidden context window. This allows the Coping Coach Agen=
t to deliver highly personalized, hyper-relevant behavioral scripts without=
 ever knowing <i data-path-to-node=3D"17,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"348">wh=
o</i> the user is or storing a user profile.</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-=
node=3D"18">5. Presentation &amp; Demo (10%)</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"19=
"><i data-path-to-node=3D"19" data-index-in-node=3D"0">(For the live demo)<=
/i>: We will demonstrate the seamless transition between the Educator Agent=
 retrieving factual data on vaping, and the Coping Coach providing a "Delay=
 &amp; Distract" UI card. Finally, we will demonstrate the invisible power =
of the Semantic Guardrail intercepting a high-risk keyword and locking the =
screen into a safe, emergency-routing state.</p><hr data-path-to-node=3D"20=
"><h1 data-path-to-node=3D"21">Document 2: Backend Architecture &amp; Imple=
mentation Guide</h1><h2 data-path-to-node=3D"22">Agentic Workflow Construct=
ion</h2><p data-path-to-node=3D"23"><b data-path-to-node=3D"23" data-index-=
in-node=3D"0">To the Engineering Team:</b>
This document outlines the backend architecture required to power Beacon. W=
e are building a modular, multi-agent pipeline. You can implement this usin=
g Python (FastAPI + LangGraph/LlamaIndex) or Node.js (Express + LangChain.j=
s).</p><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"24">1. The API Gateway &amp; Ephemeral Memo=
ry Manager</h3><ul data-path-to-node=3D"25"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"25,=
0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"25,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Endpoint:</b>=
 A single <code data-path-to-node=3D"25,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"19">/api=
/chat</code> endpoint handles all incoming frontend requests.</p></li><li><=
p data-path-to-node=3D"25,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"25,1,0" data-index-i=
n-node=3D"0">Ephemeral State:</b> The backend must <b data-path-to-node=3D"=
25,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"34">not</b> write chat histories to a permane=
nt database. Use an in-memory store (like Redis with a 30-minute TTL) or pa=
ss the session array back and forth between the client and server. Once the=
 browser tab closes, the conversation ceases to exist.</p></li></ul><h3 dat=
a-path-to-node=3D"26">2. The Semantic Guardrail (Priority 0)</h3><p data-pa=
th-to-node=3D"27">Before any generative AI touches the payload, it must pas=
s a deterministic safety check.</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"28"><li><p data=
-path-to-node=3D"28,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"28,0,0" data-index-in-node=
=3D"0">Mechanism:</b> Run the user input against a rapid keyword/regex matc=
her or a lightweight classification model.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=
=3D"28,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"28,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Trigge=
rs:</b> Flag words related to acute medical distress, self-harm, or active =
overdose.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"28,2,0"><b data-path-to-node=
=3D"28,2,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Action:</b> If triggered, immediately =
abort the LLM chain and return a strict JSON payload: <code data-path-to-no=
de=3D"28,2,0" data-index-in-node=3D"88">{"type": "emergency_override", "mes=
sage": "Standard emergency text"}</code>. The frontend will use this to ren=
der the SOS UI.</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"29">3. The Supervisor=
 Node (The Router)</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"30">If the payload passes th=
e Guardrail, it hits the Supervisor LLM.</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"31"><l=
i><p data-path-to-node=3D"31,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"31,0,0" data-inde=
x-in-node=3D"0">Function:</b> This is a fast, low-parameter model (e.g., Ge=
mini Flash). Its only job is intent classification.</p></li><li><p data-pat=
h-to-node=3D"31,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"31,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"=
0">Output:</b> It must output a strict JSON classification routing the payl=
